{
  "texts": [
    "One approach is the so-called \"bag-of-words\" model.",
    "Bag-of-words model.",
    "The bag-of word model maps each token sequence into a vector x 2 N V 0, where V is the vocabulary size, and the i-th element of x is the number of occurrences of token i in the sequence.",
    "A drawback of this approach is that the ordering of words gets lost; this issue will be discussed later.",
    "Further, each word is treated as being equally important."
  ]
}